Introduction

U.Ji is a South Korean singer, best known as a former member of the girl groups BESTie and EXID. She made her stage debut on February 12, 2012, as a member of EXID with the release of the group's debut single "Holla." However, on April 30, U.Ji announced her departure from EXID to focus on her education, as confirmed by AB Entertainment.

On July 2, 2013, U.Ji, along with former EXID members Hyeyeon and Haeryung, joined YNB Entertainment to form a new girl group, BESTie. The group officially debuted on July 11, 2013, with the single "Pitapat." However, on September 5, 2017, YNB Entertainment revealed that U.Ji and Dahye had left BESTie following the termination of their contracts.

U.Ji made her solo debut on February 17, 2015, with the digital single "Love Letter."
